Hi Grant,

Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I =
appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward.

There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure =
the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s =
responsibilities under the policy.

First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 =
including my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =
=E2=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive chemicals =
(including nearby spa products that intensified the fire). I remain =
concerned about internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and =
the potential for delayed failure or fire.

It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the =
responsibility for assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. =
Ensuring they are safe for continued use is a critical safety issue =E2=80=
=94 not just a claims matter. Tower must take responsibility for =
confirming whether these items are safe, and whether they require =
restoration or replacement.

Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s =
scope. Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or =
will they also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged linings =
(such as jib and other non-structural internal components)? This detail =
is important for understanding when and how a proper structural =
assessment of the property will take place.

Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the =
progression of the house claim. Could you please provide:

A current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
completed to date;

A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals, =
tendering, and repair;

Confirmation of the parties responsible for each stage and how updates =
will be communicated.

I look forward to your response addressing the points above.

Kind regards,
Rafaella

Let me know if you want to attach the policy wording or include any =
references to specific clauses.


> On 22 Jul 2025, at 12:19=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson =
<Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz> wrote:
>=20
> Good afternoon Rafaella,
> I wanted to take the time to thank you very much for meeting with =
Chris, David and myself at your place this afternoon. It was much =
appreciated.
> I felt that the meeting was very productive and positive as we all =
discussed the next steps and have agreed on the claim=E2=80=99s =
progression process moving forward.
> I would like to re-confirm the next steps we agreed to in writing, and =
share with all as below:
> =20
> Asset Restore to attend site as soon as possible and complete the =
process of assessing and cataloging the contents for the response of the =
contents claim. After assessment the contents which are categorised as a =
total loss will be removed from site.
> Asset Restore to strip out the property of any fire or smoke damaged =
linings or other non-structural items. This will enable a clear and =
clean structural assessment to be undertaken, from which we will produce =
a scope of works for the repairs required.
> Once we have a scope of works completed =E2=80=93 we will share this =
with you to approve before we submit to our repair panel for tendering.
> =20
> =20
> Confirming that you have notified us of the access code to be 1106.
> We will keep you updated on the above process and communicate with you =
as we move through the above steps.
> =20
> I have spoken with both our Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and =
they have said that the items you have enquired about are very unlikely =
to be affected by the fire given their location with respect to the =
proximity of the fire. I do understand that you would like to be 100% =
certain that the lithium batteries in these items have not been affected =
from the fire. The standard process in this situation is that you can =
undertake any testing of any of your items which you wish to, to obtain =
test results or a report which your insurer can consider for inclusion =
in your claims. If the test results prove any damage or loss to these =
items from the fire =E2=80=93 then your insurer will consider them =
within your claim.
> =20
> For contents items - please direct your enquiries to =
claims@tower.co.nz <mailto:claims@tower.co.nz>
> As you do not yet have a motor claim with Tower from this event =E2=80=93=
 you can also send any motor reports toclaims@tower.co.nz =
<mailto:claims@tower.co.nz> and they will respond accordingly.
> =20
> Thank you again and I strongly encourage you to call me on the number =
below with any concerns that you have with the process of the claim =
progression.
> All the best,
> Grant.=20
>=20


--Apple-Mail=_E0F9868C-5DF9-44EB-825E-6D434FFED2B9
